post_text:
La Academia Virtual del Distrito de Escuelas Primarias de Anaheim es una opción de aprendizaje 100% a distancia para familias. Se aceptan transferencias fuera del distrito. La tecnología es proporcionada a los estudiantes y la instrucción incluirá interacciones de videoconferencia SEGURAS con maestros y compañeros de clase. Si está interesado en inscribir a su hijo, llame al (714) 517-7500. Si los padres tienen preguntas, pídales que nos llamen para obtener información precisa. ¡Estamos encantados de ayudar y servir a nuestra comunidad!

*Por favor comparta
shared_text:
Anaheim Elementary School District
June 16 at 1:55 PM ·

Le presentamos para el año escolar 2020-21 nuestra nueva Academia Virtual del Distrito de Escuelas Primarias de Anaheim, que brindará a las familias la opción de que sus hijos completen su educación al 100% desde su hogar. Los mismos programas y planes de estudio increíbles de AESD, pero en un entorno virtual. Los estudiantes reciben la última tecnología para aprender e interactuar en vivo con sus maestros y compañeros de clase. Se aceptan transferencias. Por favor comparta con otros.

Continue to spread the word! The Anaheim Elementary Online Academy is a 100% Distance Learning option for families. Out-of-district transfers are accepted. Technology provided to students and instruction will include SAFE video-conferencing interactions with teachers and classmates. If you are interested in enrolling your child, call (714) 517-7500. If parents have questions, have them call us for accurate information. We are gladly here to help and serve our community! #AmazingAESD

*Please share

Yay! We made it to the last day of school! Congratulations to ALL our AESD scholars (and their families) who worked extra-hard, extra-creatively, and with extra-innovation these last few months! You should feel very proud of yourselves! (And yes, every exclamation point is merited!!!) Enjoy your summer break and we will see you on Thursday, August 13 for the first day of school. 🙂 @barton.aesd #AmazingAESD
.
.
.

Some extra-AMAZING 6th-graders that participated in our Dual Language Immersion program from Kinder to 6th grade and completed the requirements will be receiving the Pathway to Seal of Biliteracy award which will hopefully culminate when they graduate from high school with the state Seal of Biliteracy on their diploma. Great job, scholars! ¡Bien hecho! #AmazingAESD
•••••

Algunos alumnos del 6to grado extra-INCREÍBLES que participaron en nuestro programa de Inmersión en Dos Idiomas de Kinder al 6to grado y completaron los requisitos recibirán el premio Camino al Sello de Alfabetismo de Dos Idiomas, que con suerte culminará cuando se gradúen de la escuela secundaria con el Sello de Alfabetismo de Dos Idiomas en su diploma ¡Buen trabajo, eruditos! Well done!

Traditionally these employees are recognized during an AESD Board meeting, but given the current circumstances, that is not possible so we have created a video to recognize this year's Certificated Employees of the Year.

*****
Al llegar al final de dos semanas de celebrar a algunos de nuestros empleados certificados- incluyendo maestros y enfermeras durante los días de reconocimiento estatales, nacionales e internacionales- nos gustaría reconocer a los Empleados Certificados del Año del Distrito AESD. Tradicionalmente, estos empleados son reconocidos durante una reunión de la Mesa Directiva de AESD, pero dadas las circunstancias actuales, eso no es posible, por lo que hemos creado un video para reconocer a los Empleados Certificados del Año de este año.

post_text:
We are excited to share with you the wonderful news that for the second year in a row the National Association of Music Merchants or NAMM has recognized the Anaheim Elementary School District as one of the country’s Best Communities for Music! This is just one recognition that highlights the great work that AESD is doing to engage students and help them thrive. Thank you to all of our music teachers and community partners who have worked tirelessly to champion music education in our schools. #AmazingAESD
.....
Nos complace compartir con ustedes la maravillosa noticia de que, por segundo año consecutivo, la Asociación Nacional de Comerciantes de Música o NAMM ha reconocido al Distrito Escolar Primario de Anaheim como una de las mejores comunidades de música del país. Este es solo un reconocimiento que destaca el gran trabajo que AESD está haciendo para involucrar a los estudiantes y ayudarlos a prosperar. Gracias a todos nuestros maestros de música y socios comunitarios que han trabajado incansablemente para defender la educación musical en nuestras escuelas. #IncreibleAESD

In case you missed City of Anaheim- Municipal Government's recap of NAMM's Day of Service, check out the amazing day of music-making that took place at Horace Mann Elementary School. Not only did NAMM bring music industry professionals to teach our students, they also donated $10,000 to help expand our music education program!
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
En caso de que se haya perdido la recapitulación del Día de Servicio de NAMM por parte de la Ciudad de Anaheim, vea el increíble día de música que tuvo lugar en la Escuela Primaria Horace Mann. ¡NAMM no solo trajo profesionales de la industria de la música para enseñar a nuestros estudiantes, sino que también donaron $ 10,000 para ayudar a expandir nuestro programa de educación musical!

It's the best way to kick off NAMM Show every year in Anaheim. Teaching kids about music and showing how NAMM enriches our community year-round.

Thanks to all the amazing volunteers who came out!

November 25, 2019 at 9:04 AM ·

Officer Kim, having previously visited with the students at Edison Elementary School, returned this past Friday - but this time he brought Officers Prince & Zottneck with him & together they spent some time playing basketball with the Edison Eagles.

The Anaheim Elementary School District advised, "The students had the best time and couldn’t stop talking about it all day long. Definitely a memorable day for everyone at Edison. Thank you officers and Anaheim Police Department for taking some time to engage with our students!"

#copsandkids #community #basketball

The talent of AESD students, families, and staff was on full display at the Anaheim Día de los Muertos Event. This student-centered event gives students the opportunity to showcase art, language, music, dance, and culture to celebrate the universal themes of life, death, legacy, and community. Thank you SOMOS Anaheim and City of Anaheim Community Services for giving our students, families, and staff a voice in the community.

El talento de los estudiantes, las familias y el personal de AESD se exhibió por completo en el evento Anaheim Día de los Muertos. Este evento centrado en los estudiantes les brinda la oportunidad de exhibir arte, lenguaje, música, baile y cultura para celebrar los temas universales de la vida, la muerte, el legado y la comunidad. Gracias SOMOS Anaheim y City of Anaheim Community Services por brindar a nuestros estudiantes, familias y personal la oportunidad de participar.

Today 10/17 at 10:17 a.m. all AESD students and staff will be participating in the #greatshakeout by practicing: drop, cover, hold. Talk to your kids about the drill and practice at home too. Now's also a good time to review your household's emergency preparedness plan and supplies. For helpful tips and tools visit: www.shakeout.org and www.ready.gov

*****
Hoy, 10/17 a las 10:17 a.m., todos los estudiantes y el personal de AESD participarán en el #greatshakeout para practicar: agáchese, cúbrase, sujétese. Hable con sus hijos sobre el simulacro y practique en casa también. Ahora también es un buen momento para revisar el plan y los suministros de preparación para emergencias de su hogar. Para obtener consejos útiles, visite: www.shakeout.org y www.ready.gov

post_text:
So proud of our students who represented Anaheim Elementary School District at today’s community event hosted by Muzeo. We had performances by John Marshall Elementary School’s Ballet Folklorico, Gauer Elementary School’s Junior Glee Choir, and Price Elementary School’s Ballet Folklorico Alebrijes de Price. These beautiful performances showcased AESD’s commitment to give students the opportunity to use their creative voice, explore diverse cultures, and connect with their community through the arts!
. . .
Estamos muy orgullosos de nuestros estudiantes que representaron al Distrito Escolar Primario de Anaheim en el evento comunitario de hoy organizado por Muzeo. Tuvimos presentaciones del Ballet Folklórico de la Escuela Primaria John Marshall, el Coro Junior Glee de la Escuela Primaria Gauer y el Ballet Folklórico Alebrijes de Price de la Escuela Primaria Price. ¡Estas hermosas presentaciones demostraron el compromiso del distrito de brindarles a los estudiantes la oportunidad de usar su voz creativa, explorar diversas culturas y conectarse con su comunidad a través de las artes!

post_text:
Anaheim Elementary School District has been honored with the "Best Communities for Music Education" designation from The NAMM Foundation for its outstanding commitment to music education!

The recognition is awarded to districts that demonstrate outstanding achievement in efforts to provide music access and education to all students. AESD is the only K-6th elementary school district in Orange County to receive this award, and one of only two elementary school districts in the State of California and three in the nation to be recognized with this distinction.

https://anaheimelementary.org/blog/2019/03/26/2019-best-communities-for-music-education/

post_text: Today we celebrated the ribbon cutting of solar panels that were installed on the carports in the parking lots of Ross and Franklin Elementary schools thanks to the support of Anaheim Public Utilities. These solar panels have the capacity of producing 195,300 kilowatt-hours a year, which is enough for the annual energy use of about 31 homes. We hope that this innovative project sparks the curiosity of our students in the STEM fields!

post_text:
We are happy to announce that, after more than 20 years, all 23 AESD schools will now be on a traditional single-track calendar. This is something families have been asking for and there are many benefits to this change.

AESD 2019-2 Calendar: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1bSovfSODUXRaoZKgvoHhCsdCcotSdWmX/view

Nos complace anunciar que, después de más de 20 años, las 23 escuelas de AESD ahora serán operadas bajo un calendario tradicional con un cíclo único en lugar de cíclos múltiples. Esto es algo que las familias han estado pidiendo y este cambio tiene muchos beneficios.

post_text: Today was an incredible day full of learning, music, and fun at Loara Elementary School! Thanks to the NAMM Foundation our students received lessons from world renowned music teachers and participated in a jam session. Five years ago Anaheim Elementary School District had 3 music teachers; today we have 23 full time music teachers. We have expanded our elementary music program to be one of the best in the nation thanks to the support of music industry partners like NAMM. Thank you!!!
